<HEADLINE> Nepal Has 200,000 Hepatitis B Virus Carriers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 22 (Xinhua) -- About 200,000 Nepalese, or 1
percent of the country's total population, are hepatitis B virus
carriers, Nepal's official RSS news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed at a two-day workshop on hepatitis which
began here Monday.
</P>
<P>
While hepatitis A is predominantly a disease of childhood in
Nepal where almost everyone gets infected by the age of five,
hepatitis E is a common cause of jaundice among youngsters,
according to information from the workshop.
</P>
<P>
About 20 to 25 percent of pregnant Nepalese women infected with
hepatitis E die of acute liver failure, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is aimed at assessing the situation of viral
hepatitis in Nepal and presenting prevention suggestions to the
government, the RSS added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
