<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Communist Party Opens 4th Plenary Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 22 (xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
ruling Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) opened its 4th plenary
session here this morning.
</P>
<P>
The CPV's General Secretary Do Muoi presided the session and
made an important speech, official Vietnam News Agency (VNA) said
in a short Vietnamese-language report this evening.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the CPV's political bureau, Phan Van Khai,
politburo member and the prime minister of the government,
presented the guiding thought to the session and main
issues to be discussed at the plenum, VNA said.
</P>
<P>
The report said the session will focuse on economic issues to
promote industrialization and modernization of the country as well
as concrete economic and social goals set up by the 8th party
congress for the coming years.
</P>
<P>
The 4th plenum is to last until the end of december. 
</P>
</TEXT>
