<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French PM Calls Africa "Mosaic of State and Partners" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 22 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin said Monday that Africa is "a mosaic of states and
partners," rather than a monotonous entity.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Radio France Internationale in the wake
of his visit to Africa last week, Jospin said that from now on,
France should consider each African country as a partner which
should be given priority in certain fields of dialogue.
</P>
<P>
"Each (African) country arrives with its problems, its history,
its traditions, its model of development, so each time the
cooperation should be particular," he said.
</P>
<P>
During his trip to Morocco, Senegal and Mali, Jospin presented
France's new Africa policy, which is focused around three axis --
seeking "fraternity" with African countries, aiding micro-economic
projects, and playing no longer the role of "policeman" in
Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
