<HEADLINE> Pakistan Foils Bid to Smuggle Heroin Through Mail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's customs
authorities foiled an attempt to smuggle heroin through
international mail, customs sources said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 2050 grams of heroin were stealthily inserted in book
covers and inside hidden cavities made out in postcards, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The names and addresses of senders of the particular parcel
through International Mail Office, Islamabad, were found to be
fake, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
