<HEADLINE> French Government Orders 225 Air-to-Air Missiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The French government has
ordered the construction of 225 missiles to the Franco-British
military industrial group MATRA-BAe Dynamics France, said the
French Defense Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
The missiles are for the purposes of air-to-air interception,
combat and self-defense, and will be equipped on the Mirage-2000-5
chasers of the French air force from 1999 and the Rafale fighters
from 2001.
</P>
<P>
This is the third big contract between the Delegation Generale
pour L'Armement (DGA), the government agency in charge of
armaments, and MATRA-BAe.
</P>
<P>
The DGA signed a contract in October with MATRA-BAe on the
purchase of air-to-ground Apache missiles and Vesta missiles.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
