<HEADLINE> German Cartel Office Approves Adidas' Takeover of Salomon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The sports goods manufacturer
Adidas AG announced today that the German cartel office has
approved its plan to take over the French Salomon group which is
specialized in winter sports equipment.
</P>
<P>
The deal, which will cost Adidas some 2.4 billion German marks
(1.4 billion U.S. dollars), would turn the company into the No.2
sports goods maker in the world with annual sales estimated at
about 8 billion marks (4.5 billion dollars), second only to the
U.S. Nike company.
</P>
<P>
Adidas already achieved sales of nearly 5.3 billion marks (3.0
billion dollars) in the first nine months of the current business
year. With its takeover of the Salomon group, whose sales in 1996
were about 1.46 billion marks (825 million dollars), Adidas wanted
to become "the best sports goods company in the world," the
company said. 
</P>
