<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-22 18:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Ready for Arab Reconciliation Except </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 22 (Xinhua) -- While expressing its
readiness for Arab reconciliation based on clear understanding,
Kuwait today ruled out reconciliation with Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"Arab reconciliation is in the interest of Kuwait and other
Gulf states," Kuwaiti Information Minister Sheikh Saud Nasser
Al-Sabah said at a news conference after the conclusion of the
summit of the Gulf Cooperation Council here today.
</P>
<P>
He described Arab causes as the main causes of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
However, he warned of confusion in this respect. "Our position
toward the Iraqi regime is out of the reconciliation issue as it
is not a Kuwaiti (cause) but an international cause," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti minister said the Iraqi attempt to erase Kuwait
from the map is a lesson that must not be forgotten.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he expressed Kuwait's sympathy for the Iraqi people
who have been suffering from the crippling economic sanctions
imposed by the United Nations after its 1990 invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
"We are the most concerned about the suffering of the Iraqi
people, they are our neighbors, we know them more than any other
Gulf state and we are the first to send relief aid to Iraqi
refugees in Iran," said Sheikh Saud.
</P>
<P>
He expressed Kuwait's objection to "any partition of Iraq."
Instead, he said, it supports the efforts to relieve the
sufferings of the Iraqi people.
</P>
<P>
On relations between Gulf Arab countries with Iran, he
commended recent statements by Iran's President Mohammad Khatami
as "positive and in the right direction."
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that "the differences (over three islands in
the Gulf) between Iran and the United Arab Emirates will be
settled."
</P>
<P>
Iran has repeated its call for improved relations with its Arab
neighbors and has been making efforts to achieve the goal. Khatami
said last week that he is willing to visit the UAE to discuss the
disputes of the three islands.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Saud said that he is convinced that there is the
necessity to set up a security system among the Gulf states,
including Iran, which he said is a regional power. 
</P>
</TEXT>
