Jewish leader that France would be the next to be condemned for
keeping Nazi-robbed Jewish properties.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Geneva-based daily Journal de Geneve
published today, the president of the Jewish Agency, Avraham Burg,
said that the French Jews should "recover without hesitation"
their properties robbed during the Nazi occupation period.
</P>
<P>
"The declaration of Avraham Burg... is shocking enough," said
Hajdenberg. "We regret that once again the president of Jewish
Agency addressed to the leaders of the French Jewish community
through the media without even meeting them or getting their
views."
</P>
<P>
Burg, who is also president of the World Zionist Organization,
said that after Switzerland, France would be the "next target" for
recovering Jewish properties lost during World War II.
</P>
<P>
"Many many things remain to be settled. Properties confiscated,
arts works, properties," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also criticized French Jews for failing to raise the issue
in fear of a revival of anti-Semitic feeling in France. 
