<HEADLINE> Cyprus Sets Date for Presidential Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus announced today that it
will hold presidential election on February 8, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Citizens of 18 years old and above will have the right to vote,
Cypriot Assistant Chief Returning Officer George Theodorou said at
a press conference.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the Cypriots at and above this age
are eligible to vote. Previously, only those who are above 21
years old could cast ballot.
</P>
<P>
If there is more than one candidate after the first ballot, a
run-off will be held on February 15, Theodorou said.
</P>
<P>
The five-year term of incumbent President Glafcos Clerides ends
on February 28, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Six candidates, including Clerides, former president George
Vassiliou, former foreign ministers George Iacovou and Nicos
Rolandis, leader of the Cyprus National Democratic Union Vassos
Lyssarides, have announced to run for the presidency.
</P>
<P>
Speaker of the House of Representatives and leader of the
Democratic Party Spyros Kyprianou is expected to make a decision
after a meeting of the party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
