</P>
<P>
Israel had no right in deciding the fate of the West
Bank and changing the map of the occupied land because this
kind of practice was against all the agreements signed between
Israel and the Palestinians, according to a statement issued
after a meeting of top officials from Jordan and the PNA.
</P>
