All sides should respect the terms of signed agreements and
this was the basis for Israel and the Palestinians to solve their
problems, he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Erekat confirmed that the Palestinians were keen on
putting the peace process back on track by applying all the
agreements signed by both sides.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu's recent claim of the West Bank as part of
Israeli territory destroyed the peace process, said Erekat who
is here to brief Jordan on the recent development of the
peace process on the Israeli-Palestinian track. 
