<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Li Lanqing, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee, said today that the fundamental
task of language work is to standardize common language and make
it cater to economic, scientific and social development.
</P>
<P>
Language work should serve the needs of the nation's scientific
and cultural education and the emancipation and development of
productive forces, Li told a national conference on language work,
which opened in Beijing today.
