Since 1986, Putonghua, or modern standard Chinese, has been
used on a wider scale, indicating progress in the standardization
of a common language, according to Xu Jialu, director of the State
Language Work Committee, who delivered a report on the committee's
work over the past 12 years.
</P>
<P>
He said that the state plans to develop a series of laws and
regulations on the spread of Putonghua in China, to standardize
the use of Chinese characters, and to establish an efficient
information system for the Chinese language.
</P>
