<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Book "Deng Xiaoping On Journalism and Propaganda" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The book "Deng Xiaoping on
Journalism and Propaganda" has just been off the press by the
Xinhua Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
Editing work was done by Xinhua News Agency's Institute of
Journalism and approved by the Central Committee of the Party
Literature Research Center of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
The first part of the book contains extracts from Deng's
speeches and writings on journalism. The second contains related
articles.
</P>
<P>
It expresses his thoughts on the nature, role, and basic
principles of journalism and propaganda.
</P>
<P>
"Deng's thoughts on journalism are an important part of his
theory and embody his creative spirit in using Maxism to study new
situations," one editor said.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua Publishing House has plans to release books on
journalism containing the thoughts of Chinese leaders in the next
few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
