<HEADLINE> Nepal, Bangladesh Sign Agreement on Consultations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Nepal and Bangladesh signed
an agreement here Tuesday on consultations between their foreign
ministries, Nepal's official RSS news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two countries will hold regular
consultations and exchange views on bilateral relations,
international and regional matters of mutual interest, the RSS
said.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the signing ceremony, Nepali Foreign Minister Kamal
Thapa held formal talks with his Bangladeshi counterpart Abdus
Samad Azad on further expansion of mutual cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Bangladeshi foreign minister said that mutual
cooperation between Bangladesh and Nepal including economic
cooperation and the development of water resources can be further
advanced.
</P>
<P>
Later, he called on Nepali Minister for Water Resources
Pashupati Shumsher J.B. Rana and discussed cooperation in water
resources development.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with Nepali Prime Minister Surya Bahadur Thapa,
Azad handed him a letter from Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina Wajed inviting him to visit Bangladesh, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday evening, Azad called on Nepali King Birendra, Radio
Nepal said.
</P>
<P>
Azad arrived here Monday on a three-day official visit to
Nepal.  
</P>
