<HEADLINE> Chinese President Says Legal System Important For Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin has
urged officials to understand the significance of improving legal
system and improving leadership in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark today at a lecture by Professor Luo
Yuzhong of Beijing University on Scientific and Technological
Progress and Improving the Legal System, the second in a series
sponsored by the CPC Central Committee this year.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the quality of legislation and law enforcement
in the field of science and technology needs to be improved to
improve legal system.
</P>
<P>
He called science and technology the "primary productive
force", and said the 15th National Party Congress in September
developed the strategy of rejuvenating the nation through science,
technology and education to build China into a prosperous,
democratic, and civilized socialist country by the middle of the
next century.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological progress need to be increased in
economic and social development, he said, and asked leading
officials to study theory and practice for scientific and
technological progress in harmony with economic development.
</P>
<P>
He called on government departments to apply experience to laws
and to gauge the impact of future scientific and technological
progress on national strength, social and economic structure, and
on people's lives.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Li
Lanqing, and other senior Party officials were among the audience
at today's lecture. 
</P>
