<HEADLINE> China to Deepen Reform of Judicial System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Chinese
official said here today that China is to deepen the reform of its
judicial system to accelerate the process of running the country
according to laws.
</P>
<P>
Ren Jianxin, head of the Political and Legal Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, made the remark
in his work report to a national political and legal conference
held here today.
</P>
<P>
"To deepen the reform," Ren stressed, "all the law enforcement
departments must ensure seriousness and fairness in enforcing laws
by improving the mechanisms for self-restraint and outside
supervision."
</P>
<P>
Specific measures for the reform include:
</P>
<P>
-- Changing the methods of trials by increasing the
transparency and openness of court trials;
</P>
<P>
-- Further improving the system of re-investigating unjustly
sentenced cases so as to better implement existing laws and
regulations; and
</P>
<P>
-- Improving the supervision mechanism to curb corruption
within the judicial system.
</P>
<P>
Ren urged political and legal departments to give top priority
to safeguarding social and political stability, sternly crack down
on crimes that endanger state security and the safety of people
and their properties, and economic crimes, and eradicate social
evils.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 officials from the Political and Legal Committee
of the CPC Central Committee and other central departments, as
well as provincial political and legal departments attended the
conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
