<HEADLINE> 9 PKK Rebels Killed in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces have
killed nine militants of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK)
in southeastern Turkey, said an official statement released today.
</P>
<P>
The government forces exchanged fire with a group of rebels in
Yayladere town in Bingol province, and killed nine of them in the
clash, said the statement issued by the office of the Emergency
Regional Rule.
</P>
<P>
One soldier of the government forces was also killed and the
other wounded, said the statement, which did not give the date of
the clash.
</P>
<P>
It said that three PKK guerrillas were captured in provinces of
Diyarbakir, Sirnak and Tunceli in recent security operations.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting for autonomy in eastern and
southeastern Turkey since 1984, which has claimed more than 28,000
lives. 
