<HEADLINE> Israel Uncovers 3 Terrorist Cells </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Israeli General Security
Service (GSS) has uncovered three terrorist cells in the West
Bank recently and arrested some terrorists, Israel Radio reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that some 40 Hamas (Islamic Resistance
Movement) members and former Fatah (Palestine National Liberation
Movement) activists were involved in the cells. Their activities
primarily focused on petrol bomb attacks.
</P>
<P>
Four Hamas terrorists of one cell were detained in a village
near the West Bank city of Bethlehem. They have admitted to have
taken part in attacks on Israeli cars six months ago, in which no
one was hurt.
</P>
<P>
But the radio report did no give further details on the GSS
operation.
</P>
<P>
Israel demands that the Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
crack down on terrorist infrastructure, and arrest Hamas and
Islamic Jihad leaders without releasing them as a condition to
implement second redeployment in the West Bank. 
</P>
