<HEADLINE> China's Outstanding Teachers Receive Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Sixty-one Chinese teachers who
have excellent records as educators were given the "Ru Zi Niu
Golden Globe" award at a ceremony this afternoon held by the Hong
Kong Burlingame Education Foundation, in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The foundation was set up by Tang Sung Kwong, chairman of
Burlingame Group Co. Ltd., in 1994, for the purpose of backing
education in China. It mainly provides funds for primary and
secondary schools and awards for teachers who have noteworthy
achievements in teaching.
</P>
<P>
The "Ru Zi Niu Golden Globe," which was established in 1995 to
provide annual awards for teachers, has been given to 188
exceptional teachers from 31 provinces, municipalities, and
autonomous regions. This was the third time for it to be given.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Minister of the State Education Commission (SEC) Liu Bin
said that the award plays an active role in encouraging teachers
to be devoted to education, and urged society to respect teachers
and knowledge.
</P>
<P>
The foundation has donated more than 16 million yuan for
schools and improving teaching facilities in poverty-stricken
parts of Beijing and Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the ceremony were Vice-Chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress Bu He and top SEC
officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
