<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Returns to Kremlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
returned to Kremlin on Tuesday after recovering from a cold.
</P>
<P>
Ignoring doctors' advice to spend another week at a sanatorium
at Barvikha outside Moscow, Yeltsin insisted on going back to work.
</P>
<P>
"There are none of the traces of the illness left," he said.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to hold a number of working meetings in the
Kremlin before the new year, one of which is a round-table meeting
with leaders of various political parties and public movements on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the sanatorium, Moscow Yeltsin underwent a heart exam. His
bypasses were reportedly clear and his heart unaffected by his
illness.
</P>
<P>
On November 5, 1996, Yeltsin received a heart bypass operation
and spent nine months away from work during the second term of the
presidency. 
