<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientific Research Creates 100 Billion Yuan Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- China's State Science and
Technology Commission's (SSTC) scientific research programs helped
create nearly 100 billion yuan (12 billion US dollars) in output
value in agriculture and industry in the first year of the ninth
five-year plan (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
Today's People's Daily said that since 1996, China's research
programs have focused on agricultural growth, and improving
industrial and high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
The daily quoted an SSTC official as saying that more than 600
developments or products were patented in 1996, and that since
then, China has developed a hundred high-yield, high-quality
varieties of grain, and that computer-aided design has been
growing in use in 28 provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chinese computers now have 50 percent of the
Chinese market and that a robot for deep-sea work has completed a
trial run at a depth of 6,000 m. in the Pacific Ocean. 
</P>
</TEXT>
