<HEADLINE> China's Economic Growth Will Continue in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Ye Zhen, spokesman for
China's State Statistics Bureau, said that the strong economic
growth will continue next year and that China will realize its
overall economic development goal this year.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Ye said that basic industries and
infrastructure, which have been a bottleneck in the economy, will
not have a negative effect next year because of development in
the energy, transportation, telecommunications, and materials
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the 1990s, China has become a buyer's
market for consumer products, and the supply of production goods
and materials has also topped the demand.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural products have been increasing this year, allowing
a stablizing of product prices while keeping economic growth high.
</P>
<P>
Ye told Xinhua that China's inflation rate and prices of
consumer goods will remain at the lowest level of the 1990s this
year, leaving much room to co-ordinate economic growth and stable
consumer products, which can improve China's macro-economic
control measures and readjust its economic structure next year.
</P>
<P>
According to the World Bank, the average growth of world
economies will be about 3.5 percent next year, which creates a
favorable external environment for China's economy.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of China, the central bank, has lowered its
interest rate three times since the beginning of last year, to
relieve the burden on state-owned enterprises, and stimulate the
market.
</P>
<P>
Ye said that the interest rate cut has proven to be successful,
and suggests that the Chinese government is quick to respond to
market fluctuations with macro-economic controls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
