<HEADLINE> Auditing Saves State 92 billion Yuan Over Five Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese auditors have saved
the state 92 billion yuan (about 11 billion US dollars) over the
past five years, State Councilor Li Guixian said here today.
</P>
<P>
Li told an annual national conference on auditing that the
auditors turned over to the state 38 billion yuan (about 4.6
billion US dollars) collected from revenues and expenditures
against state regulations, saved six billion yuan (about 723
million US dollars) in state appropriation, and recovered 47
billion yuan (about 5.7 billion US dollars) from misappropriated
funds.
</P>
<P>
He urged auditing departments, having played an important role
in saving money for the state, increasing macro-economic control,
and promoting the campaign for a cleaner government, to better
carry out the Auditing Law and the Regulations on Carrying Out the
Auditing Law.
</P>
<P>
The regulations issued last October enhanced the authority of
auditing departments, Li pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"This is beneficial to auditing departments to do their jobs
independently and in accordance with law, and require a higher
standard for their work with a view to their increased
responsibilities defined by the regulations," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
