<HEADLINE> Russia Appeals Against Lifelong Ban upon Fedotkina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Speed Skating
Federation said here on Tuesday it had appealed against a possible
lifetime ban on skater Svetlana Fedotkina who refused an
out-of-competition doping test in Canada.
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Komarov, president of the Russian federation, argued
that no one could ask Fedotkina to undergo tests for it is against
the rules since she had been suspended and is not a competing
skater.
</P>
<P>
Fedotkina, the silver medalist in the 1,500 meters at the 1994
Lillehammer Olympics, has been serving a two-year suspension for
using anabolic steroids, which runs to January 6, 1998.
</P>
<P>
She may face a lifelong suspension as her refusal is considered
a repeated offence under the rules of the International
Speedskating Union (ISU).
</P>
<P>
ISU spokesman Fabrice Prahin said earlier in Lausanne that the
union is in the process of reviewing the case. 
</P>
