<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Ukrainian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said today that China will join Ukraine in efforts to gear
bilateral friendship and cooperation to the new century
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during an afternoon meeting with
visiting Ukrainian Prime Minister Valery Pustovoitenko.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the joint efforts of the two sides have promoted the
steady development of Sino-Ukrainian relations, and stressed that
China attaches great importance to bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
China understands and respects Ukraine's choice for development
and its domestic and foreign policies, said Jiang. He reiterated
that China will provide the Ukraine with a guarantee for nuclear
security.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also expressed appreciation for Ukrainian support for
China on issues such as Taiwan and human rights.
</P>
<P>
In terms of bilateral economic and trade relations, Jiang noted
that bilateral economic relations are generally good, with great
potential for exploring complementary advantages since the two
economies are both in a period of transformation.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral economic and trade cooperation will
continue to improve so long as the two sides engage in substantial
efforts to earnestly implement existing agreements and actively
seek new spheres and avenues for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko offered congratulations on the success of the
15th National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party, and
expressed admiration for China's rapid economic growth and
achievements in reform and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
He said Ukraine hopes to learn more from China's experiences in
this regard, and added that his country attaches great importance
to relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko said he is fully convinced that his visit will
strengthen bilateral friendship and cooperation, especially
bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang recalled his visit to Ukraine three years ago, and noted
that the friendship Ukrainian leaders and people exhibited for
China and the Chinese people left him with a deep impression. He
also noted that Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma visited China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that regular contacts between leaders of the
two countries have been of great significance in enhancing mutual
understanding and promoting the smooth development of bilateral
ties.
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko expressed his delight at being the first
Ukrainian prime minister to visit China since Ukraine gained
independence.
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko also briefed Jiang on the domestic situation in
Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Jiang in turn briefed Pustovoitenko on the current economic
situation in China, and said that China is pleased to see that the
Ukrainian government is engaged in an unremitting effort to
promote economic development and improve the living standards of
the Ukrainian people.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China cherishes its friendship with Ukraine,
and wishes the country success and prosperity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
