<HEADLINE> License Required for Import &AMP; Export of CD Making Equipment in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The new requirement that
licenses are needed for the importation into or exportation from
Hong Kong of equipment for manufacturing optical disks including
compact disks will become effective from next Monday, it was
announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The new requirement under the Import and Export (General)
Regulations is aimed at preventing Hong Kong from becoming a haven
for the manufacture of pirated optical disks," said a spokesman of
Hong Kong's Trade and Industrial Bureau Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The new measure will discourage the smuggling of optical disk
manufacturing equipment into or out of Hong Kong. It will also
enable Customs officers to better trace the origin and destination
of legally imported equipment and facilitate the development of
intelligence on suspected copyright piracy activities, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Anyone who imports into or exports from Hong Kong optical
manufacturing equipment without a valid license commits an offense
and will be liable to a maximum fine of two million HK dollars
(about 256,000 U.S. dollars) and an imprisonment of up to seven
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
