<HEADLINE> Macao-HK Ferry Boat Offers Price Cut for Children, Elderly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The Far East Company that runs
the jetfoil ferry service between Macao and Hong Kong started a
price cut for children and the elderly people from Monday.
</P>
<P>
Children under 12 years and those above 60 years of age are
eligible for a 15 patacas (about two U.S. dollars) price cut for
each voyage, provided they show certificate identifying their age,
the company said.
</P>
<P>
Jetfoil ferry boat sailing between Hong Kong and Macao is the
most favored way of traveling. In the daytime the boat starts off
every 15 minutes and a single trip costs only about 50 minutes and
150 patacas (about 18.8 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The new offer of price cut is believed to aim at attracting
more Hong Kong passengers to visit Macao during the coming
holidays. About 70 percent of tourists to Macao are from Hong
Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
