<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 23 (Xinhua) -- One more new suspected
Influenza A H5N1 case reported by Hong Kong's Department of Health
(DH) on Tuesday brings the total number of cases to nine confirmed
and three suspected.
</P>
<P>
The new suspected involves a sixty-year-old woman, according to
a daily update on the influenza issued by the DH Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The woman is at present under treatment and in critical
condition, the DH statement said.
</P>
<P>
Of the nine confirmed cases, a three-year-old boy, a
13-year-old girl and a 54-year-old man have died. And of the six
others confirmed of being infected of the H5N1 virus, two have
recovered and discharged from hospital and four others are still
under treatment.
</P>
<P>
And a three-year-old girl and a six-year-old boy, suspected of
contracting the influenza, are still receiving treatment with
their condition satisfactory, the department said. 
