<HEADLINE> Hua Xia Bank Extends Loans to Shanghai Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Hua Xia Bank, a major Chinese
shareholding bank, extended a 30 million yuan loan today for the
construction of a valve supply and component center in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Valve Supply and Component Center will be jointly
established by the Shanghai Petroleum Chemical Industry Co. Ltd.,
the city's major user of valves, and the Shanghai Jinji Group, the
the largest local marketer of related products.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Jinji Group will produce valves in accordance with
buyer specifications.
</P>
<P>
Pan Buyun, director of the Shanghai Branch of the Hua Xia Bank,
said his will provide complete banking services for enterprises in
Shanghai, China's largest trade and financial city.
</P>
<P>
