which provide the opportunity for a productive partnership between
the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Highlighting the achievements of the government, Aziz said the
economy has been rehabilitated, the business confidence has grown
and external resources consolidated.
</P>
<P>
Explaining the future program of the government, he said the
objective is to rapidly increase the economic growth through
modernization of industry and agriculture in an environment which,
he said, would also allow freedom to the private sector to play
its due role in an effective manner.
</P>
<P>
Aziz urged the Saudi government to secure greater number of
workers from Pakistan to cater for its requirement. He expressed
the hope that joint efforts during this session will be helpful in
further strengthening the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Faqeeh said the existing agreements between the two countries
reflect the eagerness to promote bilateral relations through the
identification of each other's potential and the utilization of
Saudi Arabia's resources for the mutual benefit of both sides.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi minister said the private sectors of the two
countries can play a decisive and effective role in encouraging
bilateral trade and investment through mutual contacts and
dialogue.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the current session would help in exploring ways
and means of advancing bilateral relations through full
identification of potential available in both the countries.
</P>
