<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Launch National Resilience Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will conduct a
national resilience campaign starting next week to promote
awareness among the people on their role to help the country
overcome its economic problems, Information Minister Mohamed
Rahmat said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Information Ministry and the Domestic Trade and Consumer
Affairs Ministry will be involved in the campaign to ensure that
the people understand the country's economic problems and give
their support to measures taken by the government in dealing with
the situation, he told reporters here.
</P>
<P>
Under the campaign, he said, programs like documentaries and
dramas would be aired over radio and television with themes to
promote a lifestyle with emphasis on thrift and prudent spending
including preference for local products.
</P>
<P>
He said that field officers would also conduct sessions to
explain to the people the economic problems faced by the country
and seek their cooperation to help bring about a recovery.
</P>
<P>
Rahmat hoped that the press would also contribute to such
efforts to join forces with the government to revive the economy.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is facing a serious economic situation following the
sharp fall in the value of its currency and the turbulence in its
stock market over the past few months.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian government has announced a number of measures
including the deferment of several big projects and a 18 percent
cut in government spending.  
</P>
</TEXT>
