<HEADLINE> Air Victory Museum Built in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A "B52 Blitz Victory Museum" was
inaugurated Monday in Vietnam's capital city of Hanoi, marking the
the 25th anniversary of the "Hanoi--Dien Bien Phu Victory in the
Air."
</P>
<P>
The "Dien Bien Phu Victory in the Air" recalled the fight of
the Vietnamese people against the United States in the country.
</P>
<P>
Several hundred fighter-bombers and about 150 B52s operated
daily over North Vietnam between December 18-30, 1972.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese army shot down 81 American planes including 34
B52s, foiling the U.S. scheme to "bomb Hanoi back into the stone
age."
</P>
<P>
The museum, with 1,290 square meters for display, presents the
visitors to the fighting and construction traditions of the armed
forces of the capital city. 
</P>
