<DOCNO> XIE19971223.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top 10 Chinese News Events in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The editors-in-chief of 14
major Beijing-based newspapers and a news agency today selected
China's top 10 news events for 1997.
</P>
<P>
The following list is arranged in order of number of votes
received:
</P>
<P>
1. Deng Xiaoping, the chief architect of China's reform,
opening up and modernization drive, died of illness on February
19. Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), called on the whole party, army
and people of all ethnic groups to carry out Deng's behest, and
promote the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
2. The Chinese government resumed sovereignty over Hong Kong on
July 1. Chinese President Jiang Zemin and a number of other
senior officials participated in both the handover ceremony
and the ceremony marking the founding of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
3. The 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China
was held from September 12-18 in Beijing. The Congress elected the
Party's trans-century leading group with Jiang Zemin at the core,
adopted a resolution for amending the CPC Party Constitution, and
established Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guiding ideology for the
Party.
</P>
<P>
4. President Jiang Zemin paid a state visit to the United
States from October 26 to November 3. Jiang's visit, the first US
visit by a Chinese head of state in 12 years, demonstrated that
Sino-US relations have entered a new stage of development.
</P>
<P>
5. The Yangtze River was successfully dammed for the Three
Gorges Project on November 8, thereby marking completion of a
principal aspect in construction of the world's largest water
conservancy project.
</P>
<P>
6. Chongqing was approved as China's fourth municipality. On
March 14, the Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's
Congress examined and approved the State Council's proposal for
establishing Chongqing as a municipality. The move was seen as an
important government measure for implementing the strategy of
developing central and western parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
7. In his report to the 15th National Congress of the CPC,
Jiang Zemin announced the army will be down-sized by 500,000 men
over the next three years in order to accelerate China's military
modernization drive and take concrete action to safeguard world
peace.
</P>
<P>
8. The 1997 annual meetings of the World Bank (WB) and the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) were held in Hong Kong between
September 23-25. Chinese Premier Li Peng presented a speech at the
opening ceremony. The meetings, the first WB and IMF annual
meetings held in China, were the largest international conferences
held in Hong Kong following the region's return to China.
</P>
<P>
9. The Chinese government reduced average import and export
tariff rates from 23 percent to 17 percent effective October 1, or
a decrease range of 26 percent. The reduction represented an
important measure China has adopted to deepen reform of the its
foreign trade system and open wider to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
10. The Eighth National Games, the largest and most
comprehensive sports games held in China this century, opened in
Shanghai on October 10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971223.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Wine Sales Reach Record Levels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Australian wine sales in the
financial year of 1996-97 reached record levels in both Australian
and overseas markets, an official report released here said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In its Australian Wine and Grape Industry report, the
Australian Bureau of Statistics revealed that wine exports reached
a record of 154.4 million liters in the financial year ending on
June 30, 1997 up by 19 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The income from the wine exports also reached a record of 420
million US dollars, or an average of 2.61 US dollars per liter.
</P>
<P>
The United Kingdom was the largest importer of the Australian
wine, taking 72.8 million liters (47 percent of exports), followed
by the United States with 22.5 million liters and New Zealand with
16.4 million liters.
</P>
<P>
Australians also bought more Australian-produced wine, with
domestic sales reaching a record of 333.6 million liters in
1996-97, up eight percent over the previous year and one percent
higher than the record set in 1987-88.
</P>
<P>
As Australians increasingly bought home-produced wines, wine
imports fell by 33 percent from the record high of the previous
year to 13.6 million liters in 1996-97.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971223.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan's Maruso Securities Goes Bankrupt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Maruso Securities Co., a
midsize brokerage house, filed a petition Tuesday with the Tokyo
District Court for permission to start voluntary bankruptcy
proceedings, Kyodo News reported.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo-based brokerage went bankrupt after it failed to
improve its loss-ridden financial situation.
</P>
<P>
Maruso's unconsolidated pretax balance was in the red for the
third consecutive year when it closed its books in March 1997, with a
loss of 1.48 billion yen (about 11 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The brokerage's capital-to-risk asset ratio plunged recently to
near the "warning territory" despite efforts to boost the ratio by
taking out subordinate loans from affiliates, brokerage sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Subordinate loans are unsecured loans for which repayment is
secondary to other debts if the borrower goes under. Funds raised
through subordinate loans can be counted as part of a brokerage's
net worth.
</P>
<P>
The securities industry will make sure that all securities,
cash and other assets entrusted to the firm by customers be
returned through use of Compensation Fund for Safekeeping
Securities Inc. and other means, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese securities industry has been rocked by a series of
failures since the beginning of November, including Yamaichi
Securities Co. and Sanyo Securities.
</P>
<P>
Maruso, a regular member of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, is the
fifth brokerage house to collapse this year.
</P>
<P>
The brokerage, which has a workforce of some 200 people, has
been facing business difficulties due partly to the losses it
incurred as a result of its sales strategy concerning foreign
government bonds, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971223.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> VAT Improves Zambian Government Revenue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Value Added Tax (VAT) has
improved government revenue, a Zambian economist has said.
</P>
<P>
Financial Mail today quoted Kangwa Lumbwe, an economist with
Zambia Revenue Authority (ZPA), as saying that as a stable means
to collect revenue, VAT is efficient because it is neutral.
</P>
<P>
VAT alone represents five to 10 percent of Zambia's gross
national product (GDP), said the local weekly.
</P>
<P>
Such a system of revenue collection works well for a country
like Zambia because its dependence on primary commodities like
copper and coffee cannot be guaranteed, Kangwa said.
</P>
<P>
"Primary commodities like copper and coffee may be volatile
and therefore not a good source of revenue for Zambia," said
Kangwa.
</P>
<P>
According to the economist, VAT's broad-based nature protects
revenue collection from fluctuation in the markets, which means
revenue collection remains stable even when there are
fluctuations in the markets.
</P>
<P>
The broader the tax base, the lower tax individuals pay, and
consequently, the less impact it has on them, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, Kangwa noted, ZPA has been expanding its tax base and
continues doing so under difficult circumstances to the extent
that the people are frustrating their efforts.
</P>
<P>
World over, an increasing number of countries are adopting VAT
and the World Bank as well as the International Monetary Fund
(IMF) have encouraged countries opting to have a broad revenue
collection to apply it, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
The system is spread all over Zambia and the trend is self
policing, said the economist, adding that it gives fuller relief
on exports, thereby boosts investment, avoids double taxation from
cascading as well as arbitrary valuation uplifts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971223.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Little Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended a
 little weaker Tuesday in Sydney, weighed by concerns that the
domestic economy would suffer adversely from the ongoing economic
crisis in Asia,  particularly in the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 65.28 US cents, down from 65.38
 previously. During the day it traded between 65.12 and 65.40 US
cents.
</P>
<P>
The narrowness of the range reflected subdued market conditions
usual ahead of the Christmas holidays, traders said.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended today at 85.18 Japanese yen, from
84.91 yen previously, and at 1.1629 German marks, from 1.1660
marks.
</P>
<P>
Standard &AMP; Poor's (S&AMP;P) lowered South Korea's long-term foreign
currency rating to B-plus, from BBB-minus, and its local currency
rating to BBB-minus, from A-minus. South Korea's ratings remain on
CreditWatch with negative implications.
</P>
<P>
The news had sent the South Korean currency, the won, into a
downward spiral to 2,000 to the U.S. dollar, the first time in
history it has touched that level.
</P>
<P>
It also sparked a 13.7 percent appreciation in the Australian
dollar against the won, in one session. Against the won, the local
unit closed at 1,282.10, up from 1,105.48 previously.
</P>
<P>
South Korea accounts for about 9.0 percent of Australia's
exports while Malaysia accounts for 2.9 percent. Around 60 percent
of Australia's export output goes to the Asian region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
