<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Free of Mad Cow Disease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- No cases of mad cow disease
have been reported in China, according to the Ministry of
Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The clean slate is attributed to a series of preventive
measures introduced in recent years, ministry officials said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture has issued two circulars prohibiting
the importation of cows, cow embryos, beef and products from
countries with verified cases of the mad cow disease.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to implement effective measures to prevent
the mad cow disease from surfacing in any part of the country and
protect the healthy development of animal husbandry, they said.
</P>
<P>
The mad cow disease has spread to 12 countries since the first
case was reported in Britain in 1985.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
