<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iida Wins WBA Junior Bantamweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Satoshi Iida of Japan floored
Thai Yokthai Sith Oar to take the junior bantaweight title of the
World Boxing Association in Nagoya on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Scoring his first round knockout, Iida went to take the title
on a unanimous decision after a complete 12-round bout.
</P>
<P>
Judge Erkki Meronen of Finland scored it 115-112, Waldemar
Schmit of Puerto Rico 115-111 and Rodolfo Maldonado of Panama
114-113, all for Iida.
</P>
<P>
Iida, 28, who ranked second in the WBA category, knocked down
the 22-year-old champion with a left straight to the face late in
the first round.
</P>
<P>
Yokthai, in his fifth defense of the title won from Venezuelan
Alami Goitia in Thailand on August 25, began his comeback efforts
in the fourth round.
</P>
<P>
But Venezuelan referee Enzo Montero penalized Yokthai one point
in the sixth and again in the ninth for low blows.
</P>
<P>
In the last three rounds, Iida sidestepped and clinched to ward
off Yokthai's desperate attacks.
</P>
<P>
In the 11th round, Yokthai attacked the fatigued Iida with a
series of blows, but couldn't land a decisive punch.
</P>
<P>
It was Iida's 23rd victory, including 11 by knockout, against
one defeat and one draw. Yokthai has 14 victories, including
eight by knockout, against one defeat and one draw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
