<HEADLINE> Silk Group Company Founded in Jiangsu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-eight silk companies in
Jiangsu Province, China's silk base, have formed a group to
increase mutual benefits and end fierce and disorderly competition.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu currently produces and exports some 25 percent of China's
silk. However, chaotic competition resulting from some producers
selling at below cost prices has reduced both profits and
exports for numerous companies over the past four years.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Donggui, general manager of the Jiangsu Provincial Silk
Group, said that his group has total assets of 3.14 billion
yuan and annual sales revenue of 4.46 billion yuan. The group has
holdings in 28 companies and has established cooperative
relations with an additional 58 companies.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted the diversified group can easily cover
the provincial silk sector's major business activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
