<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Some 80 percent of urban
residents living below the poverty line in north China's Hebei
Province have received government subsidies, according to a
provincial labor department official.
</P>
<P>
By the end of November, Hebei had distributed 341 million yuan
in subsidies to 79.6 percent of 253,000 people who had earned salaries
below minimum standards for six successive months, or who had
been laid-off.
</P>
<P>
Subsidies are designed to raise income levels to standards
set by the government.  
