<HEADLINE> Shandong Attracts 14.5 Billion US Dollars In Foreign Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investors had pumped
over 14.5 billion US dollars into over 20,000 firms in east
China's Shandong Province by the end of October this year,
according to a provincial government official.
</P>
<P>
The official with the Provincial Commission of Foreign Trade
and Economic Relations told overseas business people attending a
recent meeting that contracted foreign investments stood at 29.5
billion US dollars.
