<HEADLINE> EU Remains Biggest Market for Zambia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) remains
Zambia's biggest market for non-traditional exports (NTEs) this year,
accounting for 36.7 percent or 87.8 million U.S.Dollars of the NTEs
in the first ten months this year, Zambia's Financial Mail
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The total NTEs during the first 10 months amounted to 239 million
dollars, which can greatly help the country to improve foreign
currency earnings given that its earnings from copper are
expected to decline, said the weakly paper published today.
</P>
<P>
The Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa absorbed the
second largest proportion of Zambia's NTEs, accounting for 29.7
percent or 71 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The paper cited information from the Ministry of Finance's real
sector data as saying that bilaterally, Britain and South Africa are
the two biggest markets for Zambia's NTEs with exports to Britian this
year reching 45.5 million dollars while those to South Africa reached
41.1 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Other major export markets are Germany and the Democratic Republic
of Congo with exports amounting to 29.2 million and 26.2 million
Dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Asia is another emerging market for the country's NTEs with India
taking in exports worth 20.9 million Dollars, while Hong Kong only
accounted for 1.1 million Dollars, according to the paper. 
</P>
