<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive a soft
loan of 11.4 million U.S. dollars from Spain for the
telecommunication sub-package of the Jamuna Bridge Railway Link
project, 130 kilometers northwest of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to this effect was signed in Madrid last Friday,
the national news agency BSS reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
With a total cost of 800 million dollars, the
4.8-kolometer-long Jamuna Bridge on the Jamuna River, the largest
river in the country, is expected to be formally opened in June
next year.
</P>
<P>
The economic rate of return from the project may stand at 22
percent annually since it is to be a multipurpose facility
provider for traffic movement, railway, power, gas and
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh has so far received 600 million dollars for the
bridge from the World Bank, the Asian Development Bank and the
Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund of Japan.  
