<HEADLINE> Former Residence of Li Zongren Opens to Public </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The former residence and
official mansion of Li Zongren, a senior official of the former
Kuomintang government, has opened to the public in Guilin, a
scenic city in southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Li, who was born in Guilin, served as vice-president and acting
president of the former Nanjing Kuomintang government before the
founding of New China in 1949. He went to the United States in
December 1949 and stayed there for 16 years.
</P>
<P>
Li returned to China in 1965, and passed away in Beijing on
January 30, 1969.
</P>
<P>
Located in Lianjiang Town, Lingui County, his former residence
covers 5,060 square meters and is a brick-and-wood two-story
house. His villa-style official mansion in Guilin's urban area
covers 4,321 sq m. 
