<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Savings Deposit First Choice in Money Management for Urbanites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Urban Chinese citizens still
take it a first choice in managing their money to store their
money in banks, according to a survey carried on today's "Beijing
Youth Daily".
</P>
<P>
The survey carried out in seven cities such as Beijing,
Shanghai, Guangzhou, Wuhan, Chongqing, Xi'an and Shenyang showed
that 99 percent of the household respondents in these cities
have savings deposit, which accounts for 64 percent of all their
money.
</P>
<P>
Another survey on 15,600 households in the country's 71 cities
also showed that most urban residents take savings deposit as their
first choice in a bid to guarantee their basic living expenses.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, 40.8 percent of the respondents said
that they save money to support their children's study. Another
33.8 percent expressed that they do so to meet daily expenses,
and some 30 percent of them said that they save money when they are
needy in case of illness or unexpected accidents, another
19.3 percent said that they deposit money as their own old-age
pension.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that the income of Chinese citizens has
increased by two-folds since the implementation of reform and
opening up, with the per household capital volume standing at
22,300 yuan (over 2,686 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The survey said that most of the respondents said that they
do not want use their savings deposit or invest part of the
deposit in financial market when the prices remains stable.
</P>
<P>
Over 50 percent of the respondents said that they have
never thought of or will not use their savings deposit for other
purposes in case of lower interests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
