<HEADLINE> 15 Bangladeshis Hurt in Plane's Emergency Landing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 people were injured
when a Bangladesh airliner with 84 passengers on board made an
emergency belly landing on Monday night at the Sylhet Osmany
Airport, some 200 kilometers north of here.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to hospital in Sylhet Town, 15
kilometers from the airport and no deaths have been reported.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft of the Bangladesh national airlines, Biman, left
Dhaka for Sylhet at 10:10 PM Monday and had to make a near-crash
landing a little more than half a hour later due to heavy fog at
the airport, according to Biman officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
