<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jet Skis to Be Banned in Phuket, Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The local authorities in
southern Thailand's Phuket Province will ban jet skis in the
province beginning January 1 next year, a local newspaper
reported.
</P>
<P>
The local authorities decided to impose the ban in the resort
province following complaints from tourism business operators
about the noise, The Bangkok Post said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Besides the noise, jet ski racers also often venture too close
to the shore, posing a threat to beachgoers, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The ban is expected to adversely affect more than 1,000 people
in the ski business there, who strongly oppose the ban and have
urged the authorities to review it or allow them to operate far
from the shore.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
