<HEADLINE> Russia to Shoot 100 Films in 2005 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The Russian government has
approved a plan which sets the goal of shooting 100 films in the
year of 2005 in an effort to regain its past glory in film
industry.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the third Plenary Session of the Union of Cinema
Workers of Russia, Russian Prime Minister Oleg Nikolayevich
Sysuyev pledged more government support to boost the country's
film industry.
</P>
<P>
Under the development plan, more than 100 cinemas in Russian
cities will be renovated.
</P>
<P>
Since 1999, the plan stipulates, the Russian government will
allocate funds to the main filmmaking colleges in the country for
their equipment upgrading. 
</P>
</TEXT>
