<HEADLINE> Savelyev Awarded Hero Medal by Yeltsin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
awarded Colonel Anatoly Savelyev the title of Hero of Russian
Federation in recognition of his brave deeds in his life-time.
</P>
<P>
Savelyev, 51, a senior member of the Federal Security Service
(FSB), died on December 20 during a police operation to rescue a
Swedish diplomat who was kidnapped by a hostage-taker.
</P>
<P>
The highly-decorated officer, veteran of a string of
high-profile hostage situations, had replaced Swedish Embassy
commercial attache as the kidnapper's hostage and was struck by
several shots when FSB marksmen opened fire. He was taken to
hospital but died soon after.
</P>
<P>
There were three hostage dramas in 10 days on the Russian
territory. On December 10, a 59-year-old retired pensioner
hijacked a civilian airliner taking the 140 people on board
hostage. He was also overpowered by Savelyev alone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
