<DOCNO> XIE19971223.0214 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Effective Control on Pneumoconiosis In Yunnan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan
Province has scored remarkable progress in the control and
treatment of occupation diseases over recent years.
</P>
<P>
The incidence of pneumoconiosis, the disease which poses a
major threat to local workers, has dropped drastically.
</P>
<P>
A test conducted in the Kunming Iron and Steel Corporation, the
largest of its kind in the province, showed that the incidence of
pneumoconiosis has reduced from former 10 percent in 1986 to the
current three per thousand.
</P>
<P>
Only 350 patients of pneumoconiosis were found in the
metallurgical sector during the 1986-1997 period, representing a
drastic drop compared to the 2,000-plus in the 1976-1986 period.
</P>
<P>
In Yunnan Province, which is a major metallurgical and coal
industrial base of China and its southwestern region as well, dust
produced by local mines and industrial enterprises is the main
cause for the disease.
</P>
<P>
However, the efforts that have been made by local state-owned
enterprises to improve the working and living conditions of their
employees have contributed greatly to the control of the disease.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, some enterprises have established the health files
for their miners and other workers and conduct regular medical
examinations among them.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
