<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cement Plant to Be Set Up in Southern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka and India will
jointly set up a cement plant in Southern Province of Sri Lanka
next February with an investment of 40 million U.S. dollars,
reports reaching here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The plant will be built at Nugaduwa in Galle District.
</P>
<P>
The Southern Development Authority (SDA) of Sri Lanka and an
Indian company, Saurashtra Cement, have signed an agreement on the
joint venture.
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, the SDA will have a 20-percent share of the
company in lieu of the land lease and other infrastructure
facilities for the project.
</P>
<P>
The factory is expected to begin production in November 1998
and its annual output will be around 430,000 metric tons.
