<HEADLINE> British Petroleum Taps Ukrainian Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, December 22 (Xinhua) -- British Petroleum (BP) is
planning to invest 50 million U.S. dollars over the next 18 months
in developing a gas field in Ukraine's Dnipro-Donetsk Basin,
reports said Monday..
</P>
<P>
State Geology Committee Chairman Sergy Goshovsky said the
meeting between Ukrainian Prime Minister Valery Pustovoitenko and
BP Managing Director Dick Olver had yielded an agreement over the
investment. Pustovoitenko anticipated the creation of a
Ukrainian-British gas extraction joint venture to develop the
field.
</P>
<P>
British Petroleum first started prospecting for gas in the
Dnipro-Donetsk Basin last March. Results of preliminary surveys
say the field holds 500 billion cubic meters of gas, with perhaps
more than twice that amount still unexplored.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted BP officials as saying that by 2015 the field
could be producing 50 billion cubic meters per year, more than
half of Ukraine's present annual consumption of gas. 
</P>
