Bombardier, which is supported by the Exporting Credit Bank of
Canada, Mendoca said.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract, Embraer should turn out the first two jets
in February 1998 and release other 22 jets along that year.
</P>
<P>
The ERJ-145 jet, created by Embraer, is a kind of 50-seat
commercial aircraft.
</P>
<P>
Mendoca announced that the BESD will grant Embraer a
100-million-dollar credit to manufacture a 37-seat airliner.
</P>
<P>
Embraer, a company with 4,200 employees, achieved an export of
600 million dollars this year and is expected to earn 1.2 billion
dollars in foreign sales over 1998. 
