<HEADLINE> 10,000 Swans Wintering at Yellow River Delta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Over 10,000 swans are wintering
in rivers and reservoirs at the Yellow River Delta in east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The delta was once a barren and sandy area without any birds
living before the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) set up a
20,000-ha horse-raising farm in the middle 1950s.
</P>
<P>
The PLA soldiers started to plant trees when they moved
there. Up to date, they have afforested an area of 8,000 ha. Every
year, thousands of swans fly to this "ideal home" to winter from
November to April next year, starting from the early 1990s.
</P>
<P>
No swan has ever been hurt there thanks to the protection of the
soldiers. Moreover, many swans in sickness got recovered with the
help of the soldiers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
