<HEADLINE> Chile: Air Traffic to Grow 4 Times Heavier by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Air traffic in Chile is
expected to move four times more passengers in 2000 than a decade
ago, said a government official on Monday.
</P>
<P>
By the last year of the century, said Transportation and
Telecom Minister Claudio Hohmann, nine million passengers in the
country are likely to take plane when they travel.
</P>
<P>
Airline passengers in Chile amounted to six million this year,
of which 2.9 million went on international flights and 3.1 million
on national routes, Hohmann said while projecting the growth.
</P>
<P>
The international and domestic travelers this year, he noted,
increased 20 and 30 percent respectively compared with 1996.
</P>
<P>
By region, passengers to and from Asia were up 52 percent,
followed by Latin America with 23 percent plus; Europe with 15
percent and United States and Canada with 14 percent. 
</P>
