<HEADLINE> Southwest Chinese City to Host Lantern Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Zigong City in southwest
China's Sichuan Province is to host the Fifth International
Dinosaur Lantern Show from January 21 to March 9, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The show will exhibit more than 60 sets of huge lanterns and
nearly 10,000 handicraft lanterns. A number of lanterns from
20-plus countries and regions will be also displayed.
</P>
<P>
The city is famous for its lantern shows, which started as
early as in the Tang Dynasty (618-907). Since the 1960s, the city
has hosted 11 large-scale lantern shows. Its lanterns have been
exhibited in 38 cities across China and in seven countries and
regions including Singapore, Thailand and Japan, with an
attendance of more than 40 million people.
</P>
<P>
During the show, the city will also sponsor a trade fair.
