<HEADLINE> Thousands of Dead Fish Spotted in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Some dead fish, 3,000 of
them, have been spotted in the ecological park of Buenos Aires,
said Argentina's Maritime Prefecture on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The authorities attributed the mortality of fish, found on
Sunday, to gusts of rainy wind above 38 kilometers per hour on
Saturday, and to the lowering of the water's temperature.
</P>
<P>
Most of the dead fish are middle-sized Sabalos, known locally
as "Barreros."
</P>
<P>
It is the third time that a great amount of dead fish is
discovered in the coastal area of this capital city, which arises
the government's concern, said the prefecture. 
</P>
