<HEADLINE> New Plasterboard Production Line For Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese-designed
plasterboard production line started operation recently in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
A panel from the State Administration for Building Materials
and other departments has just completed an appraisal of the line,
which is owned by Beijing New Building Materials Public
Ltd. (BNBM).
</P>
<P>
The production line, the second of its kind for the company, is
capable of producing 20 million sq m of plaster boards a year. The
operation of the new production line will reduce production cost
and improve competitiveness of the company's products on the
market, the company executive said.
</P>
<P>
BNBM is China's biggest base for producing new-type building
materials and at present, its products hold more than 50 percent
of the country's plaster boards market share.
</P>
<P>
Corporate sources say that two other technical upgrading
projects are being built in the company. A mineral wool acoustic
ceiling production line is under production and is expected to
start operation on July 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe that the construction of the two projects will
greatly boost the country's new-type building materials
industry when completed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
