<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price Continues to Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The average price of the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC)'s seven crude
oils dropped to 16.75 U.S. dollars per barrel last week from 17.23
dollars a week earlier.
</P>
<P>
The organization's secretariat said Monday that since early
this year, the average price of OPEC's crude oil stood at 18.77
dollars per barrel, 1.52 dollars lower over the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark price set by the organization is 21 dollars per
barrel. 
