<HEADLINE> Designs for Major Architectural Projects on Display </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Designs for 82 major
architectural projects, including cultural facilities, squares and
office buildings in the Chinese capital city have been on display
here.
</P>
<P>
The Fourth Architectural Design Exhibition has featured more
culture-related projects than the three previous ones, with
designs of museums, teaching and research facilities, and media and
publication programs accounting for one of third of the total.
</P>
<P>
On display are outstanding designs such as a 30,900-sq-m
Chinese Modern Literature Museum featuring the traditional Chinese
garden style, a cluster of buildings for the Science College of
Qinghua University which will be in perfect harmony with existing
buildings in the Qinghua campus, which is an established example
of good architecture among Chinese universities.
</P>
<P>
Three planned squares have caught the attention of architectors
and the public. Two of them, the Xidan Cultural Square and the
Yuyuantan Park Square, will be along the Chang'an Avenue -
Beijing's east-west thoroughfare - just like the Tian'anmen
Square, and the third in front of the Beijing West Railway Station.
</P>
<P>
The annual exhibition not only displays latest designs by local
architecture, but also feature a series of lectures and a
selection of the best designs. More important, it provides a
chance for public participation in the capital's designing.
</P>
</TEXT>
