<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi's Sugar Production to Hit 2.6 Million Tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region is expected to produce 2.6 million tons of cane
sugar this year.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the growing area of sugar canes has
amounted to 460,000 hectares in the region this year, a rise of
about 6,666 hectares over last year's comparable figure. Some 24
million tons of sugar canes will be harvested for sugar
production, up 10 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi is a major sugar production base of China and has been
placed the first in the country for cane sugar output in a
succession of five years. It produced 2.35 million tons of cane
sugar last year.
</P>
<P>
To improve economic efficiency, different localities of the
region have expanded reform in sugar-making enterprises over the
past years, and many sugar-making factories have united to tap
business potentials.
</P>
<P>
The overall strength of the sugar-making industry has been
strengthened thanks to the implementation of a unified management
and marketing measures.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the state has also practiced a range of macro
control measures, including controlling sugar imports, cracking
down on sugar smuggling and initiating a special fund to support
implementation of a provisional sugar reserve system, making it
possible for sugar to enter the market in a balanced way according
to changing market demands.  
</P>
</TEXT>
