<HEADLINE> EF Language Wins Whitbread Yachting Third Leg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- EF Language won the third leg
of the Whitbread Round the World race Tuesday in the closest
finish in the history of the competition.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish entry crossed the finish line in Sydney Harbor at
1:39 a.m. (1439 GMT Monday), just five minutes ahead of Swedish
Match.
</P>
<P>
With American skipper Paul Cayard at the helm, the boat fought
inch by inch to get past Swedish Match, and Cayard was forced to
replace a broken spinnaker pole during the last hours of the race
but was able to put his yacht into the overall lead.
</P>
<P>
It took nine days, nine hours and nine minutes, 20 seconds for
EF Language to complete the 2,250 mile leg from Fremantle to
Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The American yacht Chessie Racing was third, just 53 seconds
behind Swedish Match, with Merit Cup fourth and Innovation
Kvaerner fifth.
</P>
<P>
EF Language, which also won the first leg from Southampton,
England, to Cape Town, South Africa, secured 105 points with the
victory and took the overall lead in the eight-month, nine-leg
competition. 
