<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 23 (Xinhua) -- At least a million workers
in Guangzhou, the capital of south China's Guangdong Province,
have taken part in a self-education campaign that began a decade
ago.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong has been a leader in the nation's opening-up drive
and is a step ahead of other provinces in using the results of the
country's economic reforms, which has given local workers greater
awareness of the importance of knowledge.
</P>
<P>
The campaign has attracted personnel from state-owned and
collectively-owned enterprises, managerial and technical people,
and laid-off workers, and it has a number of forms, ranging from
self-education through reading, training classes, and lectures to
special knowledge contests.
</P>
<P>
The city government also has a special regulation that gives
detailed rules on awards available to self-educated people.
</P>
<P>
