<HEADLINE> Chinese Ethnic Minority Region Has Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region reported a record 1997 grain harvest of 16.6
billion kg, up 500 million kg on the 1996 harvest despite the
adverse effects of various natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
The region is one of China's major rice producers, with rice
accounting for 85 percent of its total annual grain output.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi places priority on rice production. The local farmers
are encouraged to apply advanced techniques in rice planting. This
has contributed greatly to raising the per hectare output.
</P>
<P>
The region has also extended great effort to train farmers and
grass roots officials in scientific farming. As a result, nearly
5.6 million people, or 85 percent of the total rural labor force,
have received special training.
</P>
<P>
Experimental high-yield fields have played a major role in
increasing output. The region set aside some 600,000 ha of
high-yield farmland as experimental sites for new agronomic
techniques, with related projects yielding encouraging results.
</P>
</TEXT>
