<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Pillar Industries Witness Continued Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Six pillar industries in
Shanghai, China's economic powerhouse, generated a total output of
164.2 billion yuan for the first three quarters of 1997, and
accounted for a record 51.8 percent of the city's total industrial
output value.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that market-oriented production industries
manufacturing automobiles, electronic telecommunications
equipment, power plant equipment, refined chemicals, iron and
steel and electrical appliances had a production-sale ratio of
97.7 percent, up 0.5 percentage points on the last year's same
period.
</P>
<P>
The automobile manufacturing industry, in particular, recorded
a 17 percent rise in pretax profits on the previous year's same
period, and accounted for 30 percent of the total volume for the
six pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
But, The growth rate of the six pillar industries for the
January-November fell five percentage points on the previous
year's same period, with their contribution to Shanghai's
industrial sector falling by 13 percentage points. Economists
point out that the six industries will need to develop and market
new products in order to maintain the current growth momentum.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
