<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street
survived a midday retreat and ended higher today with the Dow
Jones industrial average rising 63.02 points to 7,819.31.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 529.95 million
shares as against 782.06 million of Friday's session, the second
busiest day in the history of NYSE.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 6.93 to 953.71, and
the NYSE composite index rose 3.09 to 500.48.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index, dominated by technology shares,
gained 7.29 to 1,532.03.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange composite index rose 2.39 to 663.07.
</P>
<P>
Heading into the holiday-shortened week, broad-market indexes
showed modest improvement across the board, according to market
analysts. 
</P>
