<HEADLINE> 5 Israelis Indicted for Maccabiah Bridge Tragedy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Israel's state prosecutors
today filed indictments against five Israelis, allegedly
responsible for the Maccabiah bridge tragedy which claimed the
lives of four Australian athletes and injured more than 60 last
summer.
</P>
<P>
The five people were charged in a Tel Aviv Magistrate's Court
with negligence and manslaughter for the July 14 bridge collapse
which occurred on the occasion of the opening of the 15th
Maccabiah Games in Tel Aviv.
</P>
<P>
Local media reported that prosecutors took the action only
after the Australians exerted pressure to speed up the indictment
process.
</P>
<P>
The five being charged are the engineer who designed the
bridge, two contractors, the head of the Games' organizing
committee, and the director of the Irgunit company which supplied
materials for the bridge.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the World Maccabi Union, organizer of the Maccabiah
Games, said that it was launching its own investigation into the
incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
