<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Release of 15 Iranians Jailed by </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Iran has called for the
release of 15 Iranians jailed in the Afghan province of Kandahar
by the Afghan Taliban militia, a senior Iranian official said
today.
</P>
<P>
Iran's special representative on Afghan affairs Alaeddin
Boroujerdi said in Rey, Tehran province that the Iranian consul
general in Jalalabad of Afghanistan, Mohammad Reza Bahrami,
recently visited the jailed Iranians and asked the Taliban to
immediately release them.
</P>
<P>
Boroujerdi said that the innocent Iranians were kidnaped by
the Taliban militia, the Iranian official news agency IRNA
reported. However, he did not give the details about how and when
the Iranians were kidnaped by the Afghan group.
</P>
<P>
Iran recognizes the government of Afghan President Burhanuddin
Rabbani as the sole legal government of Afghanistan and attacked
the Taliban for their refusal to join the peace process in the
war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
As the current chairman of the Organization of the Islamic
Conference (OIC), Boroujerdi said, Iran is intent on more
serious efforts for realization of peace in Afghanistan.
</P>
</TEXT>
