<HEADLINE> State of Emergency Declared in Western Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese President Omar
Hassan Ahmed al-Bashir today declared a state of emergency in the
three states of the Darfur Region and the adjacent West Kordofan
state to check armed looting.
</P>
<P>
According to the official Sudanese News Agency, al-Bashir has
received the recommendations of the peaceful coexistence
conference of the Darfur states, which began on December 17 in
Nyala, capital of the South Darfur state in west Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The conference has recommended the use of force to fight
against the armed plundering and enable government officials to
put an end to it.
</P>
<P>
Al-Bashir has also received the charter submitted by the Darfur
tribes, which underlines that no tribe will transgress other
tribes, and will refer cases of offense to government for action.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese president has stated that sentences passed against
looters should be executed at the very site of the offense.
</P>
<P>
He called on the citizens of the Darfur Region to undertake
their duty by immediately informing about the perpetrators and
their whereabouts.
</P>
<P>
The Darfur states have been the scenes of the armed looting.
Deterioration of security and numerous cases of plundering have
been reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
