<HEADLINE> IFC Launches 300 Million Hong Kong Dollar Global </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the launching of a 300 million
Hong Kong dollar issue under its Global Medium Term Notes program.
</P>
<P>
The 3-year notes equivalent to some 39 million U.S. dollars,
carry a semi-annual coupon of 10.25 percent per annum and an issue
price of 100.00 percent. The proceeds of the issue will be swapped
into U.S. dollars floating rate funds.
</P>
<P>
The sole lead manager is Banque Nationale de Paris.
</P>
<P>
The latest transaction brings IFC's market borrowing to about
1,781 million U.S. dollars for the fiscal year 1998, which began
on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
On September 19 this year, IFC launched a 400 million Hong Kong
dollar issue under its Global Medium Term Note program which is
equivalent to 52 million U.S. dollars. About 20 days later, IFC
increased the issue on October 9 by an additional 100 million Hong
Kong dollars, which is about 13 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and also the largest
multilateral source of financing for private sector projects in
developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
