<HEADLINE> NFU Welcomes Government Support Package </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 22 (Xinhua) - British Agriculture Minister
Jack Cunningham announced an 85 million pounds (136 million US
dollars)aid package for its beleaguered livestock industry.
</P>
<P>
The move follows widespread protests by farmers who complain
their businesses are in danger because of the high value of
sterling and the European Union ban on British beef exports.
</P>
<P>
The National Farmers' Union (NFU) welcomed the news of support
package to beef and sheep farmers, saying it is a "lifeline" to
some and bring relief to the beef sector.
</P>
<P>
But NFU President David Naish warned a level playing field
between UK and other EU farmers had not been restored.
</P>
<P>
The British government's call for a restructuring in the
European farming industry would continue, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
